Initial Assessment:
- Document time and date of incident discovery
- Identify the type of security concern
- Determine affected user(s) and device(s)
- Assess initial severity level

{% if incident_type == 'phishing' %}
Phishing Email Response:
- Instruct user NOT to click any links or attachments
- Have user forward email to security team
- Check if user clicked links or entered credentials
- If credentials entered, initiate immediate password reset
- Check for email forwarding rules added to mailbox
- Report phishing URL to security tools
- Delete phishing email from user's mailbox
- Block sender domain if confirmed malicious
{% endif %}

{% if incident_type == 'malware_alert' %}
Malware Alert Response:
- Verify the alert source (antivirus, EDR)
- Check if malware was quarantined or removed
- Run full system scan
- Check for persistence mechanisms
- Review recent file downloads and executions
- Verify no data exfiltration occurred
- Re-image device if infection confirmed
{% endif %}

{% if incident_type == 'suspicious_popup' %}
Suspicious Pop-up/Scam:
- Instruct user not to call numbers or click buttons
- Close browser or force quit application
- Clear browser cache and cookies
- Scan system for adware/malware
- Check browser extensions for malicious add-ons
- Verify no software was installed
{% endif %}

Evidence Preservation:
- Take screenshots of suspicious content
- Document user's description of events
- Note any actions user took
- Preserve logs if needed for investigation

Containment Actions:
- Isolate device from network if active threat
- Disable compromised accounts temporarily
- Block malicious URLs/IPs at firewall
- Revoke suspicious OAuth app permissions

User Communication:
- Reassure user and thank them for reporting
- Explain what happened and actions taken
- Provide guidance on recognizing future threats
- No blame - encourage continued reporting

Escalation and Documentation:
- Escalate to security team if confirmed incident
- Document incident in security tracking system
- Update user's security awareness training if needed
- Close with full incident summary
